<p>
<seg id=1> Chinese Minister OF Foreign Affairs, Tang Jiaxuan, who is officially visiting in the US on the 29th spoke at a news conference along with Senator Albright about the relationship between the US and China. </seg>
<seg id=2> Tang Jiaxuan also talked about the allegations concerning President Clinton, saying this is a US domestic concern.  China will never forget the contributions President Clinton has made towards enhancing friendship between China and the US. </seg>
<seg id=3> The following is a live report from that day, by Youkang Zhou from the Voice of America. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> All the listeners, at 11:00AM on the 29th heard President Clinton's meeting with Tang Jiaxuan, who is in Washington while officially visiting the US. </seg>
<seg id=5> The American Senator Albright held a press conference along with Minister Tang Jiaxuan around noon on the 29th in the State Conference Room, where the news about the President's meeting with Tang Jiaxuan was also announced. </seg>
<seg id=6> Albright said </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Senator Albright said that, I am very glad to tell everyone that the Chinese Minister of Foreign Affairs, Tang Jiaxuan met with President Clinton a while ago, and also announced that China had decided to sign the International agreement on Human Rights and Political rights on October 5th in New York. </seg>
<seg id=8> The Chinese Minister of Foreign Affairs, Tang Jiaxuan also expressed at the news conference that his meeting with President Clinton will have very long term effects. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> The fact is, that President Clinton's meeting with me, in my opinion accomplished a great deal. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> Currently President Clinton is involved in a scandal where many people from both inside and outside of the US criticize him for his behaviour. </seg>
<seg id=11> Some people have suggested that he should be impeached. Some people have asked him to resign.  Furthermore, some Democratic Congressmen want to separate themselves from him. </seg>
<seg id=12> However, The Chinese Minister of Foreign Affairs, Tang Jiaxuan, greatly praised President Clinton for his contribution towards enhancing the relationship between the US and China. </seg>
<seg id=13> At the news conference reporters asked Tang Jiaxuan if President Clinton's scandal will affect relations between China and the US. </seg>
<seg id=14> Tang Jiaxuan replied thus </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=15> I think this is entirely a domestic matter for the US to deal with. </seg>
<seg id=16> I would never consider that this could affect Chinese relations with the US. </seg>
<seg id=17> President Clinton himself has made valuable contributions towards developing the relationship between China and the US.  We will not forget his contribution. </seg>
<seg id=18> Myself and China sincerely hope that the relationship between the US and China continue to improve steadily and solidly based on the three agreements already signed and the announcements made in this meeting by the leaders of these two countries. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=19> Chinese officials have repeatedly expressed that Taiwan is one of China's provinces and that this is China's domestic problem. </seg>
<seg id=20> The Chinese Minister of Foreign Affairs, Tang Jiaxuan, repeatedly talked about Taiwan while attending a meeting in the UN and during his visit to Washington. </seg>
<seg id=21> At the news conference, one reporter asked  Tang Jiaxuan what is the biggest obstacle now in the relationship between China and the US.  Then Tang Jiaxuan replied thus </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=22> I think I have said many times that in regards to this area, the best thing to do about it is to deal with Taiwan in the proper way. </seg>
<seg id=23> Because Taiwan is the most sensitive and most objectionable concern in the relationship between China and the US. </seg>
</p>
